According to a report by Intel Market Research, the India Battery Module and Pack Equipment Market was valued at USD 345 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 387 million in 2025 to USD 678 million by 2032, registering a CAGR of 11.9% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust expansion as India rapidly strengthens its electric vehicle (EV) manufacturing ecosystem, supported by favorable government policies, rising investments in battery production, and increasing demand for renewable energy storage systems. The growing establishment of domestic battery manufacturing facilities and the localization of battery supply chains are creating substantial opportunities for advanced battery module and pack equipment manufacturers.
India's transition toward sustainable mobility remains one of the strongest growth drivers for the market. Government initiatives such as the Faster Adoption and Manufacturing of Electric Vehicles (FAME II) scheme and the Production Linked Incentive (PLI) scheme for Advanced Chemistry Cell (ACC) battery manufacturing have significantly accelerated investments in local battery production. As electric vehicle adoption continues to rise across passenger cars, commercial vehicles, and two-wheelers, manufacturers are expanding battery assembly capacities, driving strong demand for automated module assembly lines, welding systems, formation equipment, and battery testing solutions.
